research_municipality_step.notes: North Brunswick Township operates under the Mayor-Council-Administrator form of local government, a variant of the Faulkner Act. The Mayor is directly elected for a four-year term, and the Township Council consists of six at-large members serving three-year staggered terms. The Mayor's term ends December 31, 2027. Alvin Rich is serving as the Township Council President in 2026.
